---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Visa Sponsored Tech Jobs in Germany | Software Engineering & More"
description: "Find visa-sponsored tech jobs in Germany with relocation assistance. Browse software engineering, data science, and DevOps roles in Berlin, Munich, Hamburg and more."
permalink: /jobs-in-germany/
---

{% set country_name = "Germany" %}
{% set country_flag = "🇩🇪" %}
{% set country_slug = "germany" %}
{% set grouped = jobs | groupByCountry %}
{% set countryJobs = grouped["Germany"] or [] %}

{% block structuredData %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "{{ site.url }}/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Jobs by Country", "item": "{{ site.url }}/jobs-by-country/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Germany", "item": "{{ site.url }}/jobs-in-germany/" }
  ]
}
</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "CollectionPage",
  "name": "Visa Sponsored Tech Jobs in Germany",
  "description": "Find {{ countryJobs | length }}+ visa-sponsored tech jobs in Germany with relocation assistance.",
  "url": "{{ site.url }}/jobs-in-germany/",
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.name }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}" },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "ItemList",
    "numberOfItems": {{ countryJobs | length }},
    "itemListElement": [
      {% for job in countryJobs | limit(10) %}
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": {{ loop.index }},
        "item": {
          "@type": "JobPosting",
          "title": "{{ job.position }}",
          "datePosted": "{{ job.post_date }}",
          "validThrough": "{{ job.post_date | validThrough }}",
          "description": "{{ job.position }} at {{ job.company }} in {{ job.location }}. Visa sponsorship and relocation assistance included.",
          "employmentType": "FULL_TIME",
          "hiringOrganization": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "{{ job.company }}",
            "logo": "{{ site.url }}{{ job.logo }}"
          },
          "jobLocation": {
            "@type": "Place",
            "address": {
              "@type": "PostalAddress",
              "streetAddress": "",
              "addressLocality": "{{ job.location | extractCity }}",
              "addressRegion": "{{ job.location | extractCity }}",
              "postalCode": "",
              "addressCountry": "DE"
            }
          },
          "url": "{{ job.description }}"
        }
      }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    ]
  }
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

{# Hero #}
<section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50 to-white dark:from-gray-900 dark:to-gray-950 py-12 md:py-16">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors">Home</a>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
      <a href="/jobs-by-country/" class="hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors">Jobs by Country</a>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
      <span class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-medium">Germany</span>
    </nav>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
      <span class="text-5xl">{{ country_flag }}</span>
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">
          Tech Jobs in Germany
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">
          {{ countryJobs | length }} visa-sponsored positions with relocation assistance
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-6">
      <span class="badge badge-visa">Visa Sponsorship</span>
      <span class="badge badge-reloc">Relocation Assistance</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
        <i data-lucide="map-pin" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
        Berlin, Munich, Hamburg & more
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Job Listings #}
<section class="py-12">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
      <h2 class="section-heading">All Positions</h2>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">{{ countryJobs | length }} jobs</span>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      {% for job in jobs %}
      {% if "Germany" in job.location %}
      <div class="job-card">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start gap-4">
          <img src="{{ job.logo }}" alt="{{ job.company }}" class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg object-cover shrink-0" loading="lazy" onerror="this.src='/favicon/android-chrome-192x192.png'">
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-1">{{ job.position }}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">{{ job.company }}</p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-1 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">
              <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
                <i data-lucide="map-pin" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
                {{ job.location }}
              </span>
              <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
                <i data-lucide="clock" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
                {{ job.post_date | timeAgo }}
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              {% if job.reloc %}<span class="badge badge-reloc">{{ job.reloc }}</span>{% endif %}
              {% if job.visa %}<span class="badge badge-visa">{{ job.visa }}</span>{% endif %}
              <span class="badge badge-contract">{{ job.contract }}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a href="{{ job.description }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="job-card-apply">
            Apply <i data-lucide="external-link" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 ml-1.5"></i>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# SEO Content #}
<section class="py-12 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900/50">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Working in Germany as a Tech Professional</h2>
    <p>
      Germany is Europe's largest economy and one of the most attractive destinations for international tech talent. Cities like Berlin, Munich, and Hamburg host thriving tech ecosystems with companies ranging from global enterprises to fast-growing startups. The country's strong industrial base, combined with a booming digital sector, creates abundant opportunities for software engineers, data scientists, and DevOps professionals.
    </p>
    <p>
      The <strong>EU Blue Card</strong> is the primary visa pathway for skilled workers from outside the EU. It offers a streamlined application process, and tech professionals typically qualify due to competitive salaries meeting the required threshold. Germany also introduced the <strong>Chancenkarte</strong> (opportunity card) in 2024 for job seekers. Most tech companies in major cities operate in English, though learning German significantly improves daily life and career advancement.
    </p>
    <p>
      Germany offers excellent work-life balance with strong labor protections, typically 30 days of paid vacation, public healthcare, and generous parental leave. The cost of living varies — Berlin remains relatively affordable compared to London or Amsterdam, while Munich is pricier but offers proximity to the Alps and a high quality of life.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

